                <fr:title text="Sylow &quot;Development&quot; Theorem">Sylow "Development" Theorem</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">I. Martin Isaacs <fr:link href="/isaacs-2008-finite/" title="Finite Group Theory" uri="http://localhost:8000/isaacs-2008-finite/" display-uri="isaacs-2008-finite" type="local">Finite Group Theory</fr:link> Theorem 1.14 (Sylow D-Theorem)</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gr-004O/" title="p-Group" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-004O/" display-uri="gr-004O" type="local"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-Subgroup</fr:link> of a finite <fr:link href="/gr-000G/" title="Group" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-000G/" display-uri="gr-000G" type="local">Group</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is contained in some <fr:link href="/gr-004S/" title="Sylow p-subgroup" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-004S/" display-uri="gr-004S" type="local">Sylow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-subgroup</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>.</html:p><html:p>In other words, Sylow subgroups are "maximal" among the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-subgroups of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be a Sylow subgroup, by <fr:link href="/gr-004X/" title="Any p-subgroup is contained in a conjugate of a Sylow subgroup" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-004X/" display-uri="gr-004X" type="local">Any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-subgroup is contained in a conjugate of a Sylow subgroup</fr:link> there is a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\in  G]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P\leq  S^{g}]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|S|=|S^{g}|]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S^{g}]]></fr:tex> is another Sylow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-Subgroup of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>.</html:p><html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
