            <fr:title text="p-Group">p-Group</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">MML <fr:link href="https://mizar.uwb.edu.pl/version/current/html/group_10.html#V2" type="external">group_10:def 17</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> be a prime number. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gr-000G/" title="Group" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-000G/" display-uri="gr-000G" type="local">Group</fr:link>. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> is a <html:dfn><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-Group</html:dfn> if there is some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|G|=p^{n}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
